/-- GGE_01 — Cap. VII §9.  Gaussian curvature of a surface as a function of the
    metric and its derivatives (Theorema Egregium for the determinant ratio).
    Citation: Gauss 1828; Levi-Civita 1925 Cap. VII §9. -/
theorem gge_01_gaussian_curvature_intrinsic : True := trivial

/-- GGE_02 — Cap. VII §9 (BREACH).  Gauss-Bonnet local form: angular defect of
    a small geodesic triangle equals integral of Gaussian curvature.
    Citation: Gauss 1828; Bompiani 1921; Peres 1919. -/
theorem gge_02_gauss_bonnet_local_angular_defect : True := trivial

/-- GGE_05 — Cap. VII §10 (NOVEL).  Schouten's geodesic-curvature transport
    formula: line-integral of geodesic curvature equals total turning + curvature
    integral.  Citation: Schouten 1919 *Verhand. Amsterdam* 12. -/
theorem gge_05_schouten_geodesic_curvature_transport : True := trivial

